### Description

Using NgOptimizedImage where the ngSrc is set from signal. Then using (error) to update the src, but when the src is updated the placeholder is not applied again as my second request is taking longer, so i would like to show placeholder. It is only applied once for the first time.
Is there a way to reset the placeholder when changing the src, so that placeholder can be applied when another request is being made for new src.

Here is the bare minimum

```
ngOnInit(): void {
      this.currentImage.set(this.image());
  }
image = input<string>('');
currentImage = signal<string>('');
tryProxyImage = false

onImageError(event: Event): void {
    console.log('TAGTAG Image error', event);
    if(!this.tryProxyImage && this.image().trim().length > 0 && this.image())
    {
      const proxyImageUrl = 'http://sampleimg.jpeg';
      this.currentImage.set(proxyImageUrl);
      this.tryProxyImage = true;
    }
    else
    {
      this.currentImage.set('./assets/images/not_found.png');
      this.imageError.set(true);
    }
  }
```


TEMPLATE
```
 <img ngSrc="{{ currentImage() }}"
      fill
      (error)="onImageError($event)"
      placeholder="./assets/images/not_found.png"/>
```





